The reasoning of Nepos as to the connection between the maius imperium and the three hundred statues hardly holds good. The Athenians had no imperium beyond Attica in the days of Demetrius Phalereus.

Demetrius of Phalerum (Phalerum was the oldest harbour of Athens) was put at the head of the Athenian Oligarchical party by Cassander, Viceroy of Macedon, to govern in his interest (1317-307 B.c.) as despot. He seems to have goverued well, hut had to leave Athens on the invasion of Demetrius Poliorcetes with a large army.
